==English==

===Etymology===
'''Sephiroth''' or '''Sfirot''' is a [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] word meaning "counting", or "number", or "statistics", ('''ספירות''', [[Standard Hebrew]] '''Səfirot''', [[Tiberian Hebrew]] '''Səp̄îrôṯ''').

===Noun===
'''Sephiroth'''

# In Jewish occultism: the ten attributes that God created through which he can project himself to the universe and man.